Q3: What cmdlet would you use to get the results of a job, and how would you save the results in the job queue?

A:

Receive-Job -Id <JobID> -Keep

#Reviewed the lab question and identified two separate requirements:

#Retrieve job results

#Preserve job output after retrieval

#Reviewed job management cmdlets introduced in Chapter 14

#Identified:

Receive-Job

as the cmdlet used to retrieve output generated by a background job

#Reviewed:

Get-Help Receive-Job

to better understand available parameters

#Learned that running:

Receive-Job -Id <JobID>

retrieves job output

#Learned that job output is normally consumed when retrieved

#Observed that retrieving job results without additional parameters may prevent the same output from being viewed again

#Reviewed the purpose of:

-Keep

#Learned that the Keep parameter preserves job output after retrieval

#Verified that:

Receive-Job -Id <JobID> -Keep

retrieves job results while maintaining the output in the job queue

